<li>WordPress 4.7 or greater</li>
</ul>
<h4>From within WordPress</h4>
<ol>
<li>Visit &#8216;Plugins &gt; Add New&#8217;</li>
<li>Search for &#8216;Post and Page Builder by BoldGrid&#8217;</li>
<li>Activate Post and Page Builder from your Plugins page.</li>
</ol>
<h4>Manually</h4>
<ol>
<li>Upload the entire post-and-page-builder folder to the /wp-content/plugins/ directory.</li>
<li>Activate the plugin through the Plugins menu in WordPress.</li>
</ol>
<p>You will find a &#8216;Post and Page Builder&#8217; menu in your WordPress admin panel and find most features within the<br />
WordPress Editor.</p>
